Questions:
What will happen if you choose to withdraw from the CIRTiN-BC study at any point?
A) You will be required to pay a penalty fee for early withdrawal; 
B) Your medical care or relationship with UT Southwestern staff or doctors will be negatively affected; 
C) You will still be able to receive standard medical care without any impact on your legal rights or quality of healthcare; 
D) You will be obligated to continue participating in other unrelated clinical trials.

Correct answer: C

Which of the following procedures is considered experimental in the context of the Checkpoint Inhibitor and Radiation Therapy in Bulky, Node-positive Bladder Cancer (CIRTiN-BC) study?
A) Standard chemotherapy for bladder cancer;
B) Radical cystectomy or removal of the bladder;
C) The combination of Immune Checkpoint Inhibitor (ICI) treatment with Personalized Ultrafractionated Stereotactic Ablative Radiation (PULSAR);
D) Routine follow-up visits with a medical oncologist after surgery.

Correct answer: C

If you experience an adverse reaction or injury related to the research study, whom should you contact immediately?

A) Your primary care physician;
B) The study team at the provided contact numbers;
C) The insurance company;
D) A family member or friend.

Correct answer: B) The study team at the provided contact numbers.
